snippet.title: 'Deport Zohran Mamdani', Scream MAGA Supporters Ahead Of NYC Mayor Polls; Can Trump Do It?
snippet.description:
MAGA supporters' 'Deport Zohran Mamdani' chants have hit fever pitch ahead of the all important New York City mayoral election. Two prominent Republican lawmakers have demanded that the Department of Justice revoke the citizenship of the 34-year-old Democratic nominee, accusing him of being an “antisemitic communist who will destroy the great City of New York.” Mamdani, the son of acclaimed Indian filmmaker Mira Nair, came to the US from Uganda at the age of 7 and acquired citizenship in 2018. Trump is backing Mamdani's rival Andrew Cuomo, a Democrat who lost the primaries and is now contesting as an independent. The US President has dubbed Mamdani a '100% Communist lunatic'. But can he really strip Mamdani of his citizenship?

snippet.title: Deputy Assistant to Trump calls out Kevin Rudd’s anti-Trump tweets in first meeting
snippet.description:
Deputy Assistant to the US President Sebastian Gorka reveals he confronted US Ambassador Kevin Rudd over his past anti-Trump tweets during their first meeting.

“In my first meeting with your Ambassador, I brought up his tweets against the President, just to make sure he understands who we are and that we have very long memories and the internet is forever,” Mr Gorka told Sky News host Sharri Markson.

“I brought up his importune tweets and comments in our first meeting together … you make your bed, and you lie in it.”

snippet.title: 🔴 LIVE NOW PORTLAND BROADVIEW LOS ANGELES ICE IMMIGRATION 24HR PROTEST NYC PARADE HALLOWEEN MULTICAM
snippet.description:
PORTLAND
A court hearing is underway: a federal judge (Karin Immergut) rejected the Trump administration’s request to lift an injunction blocking National Guard troop deployment to Portland.

Also: Clark County, Washington officials are questioning why three protesters arrested in Portland were transported across state lines to their jail in Vancouver, WA. 

Current state & risk assessment

Right now, protest activity in Portland appears relatively calm, especially compared to earlier clashes: the large march was mostly peaceful; the later ICE facility confrontation had some force used by federal agents, but did not result in mass arrests on the 21st.

The legal battle over federal/troop deployment remains active and could alter the dynamics of protest + enforcement in the coming days.

For someone in Portland: keep an eye on the South Waterfront (ICE facility area) and downtown waterfront as potential flash-points if protests resurge or enforcement escalates.

Stay alert for disruptions to traffic, public transit, and potential use of crowd control measures (tear gas, pepper balls) in areas where protesters gather.

snippet.title: Aryna Sabalenka FURIOUS After Coco Gauff RECEIVES HUGE ROLEX CONTRACT!
snippet.description:
Aryna Sabalenka FURIOUS After Coco Gauff RECEIVES HUGE ROLEX CONTRACT!

The moment Coco Gauff signed with Rolex, the tennis world froze. Not because it was unexpected — but because it was monumental. A deal like this doesn’t just happen. Rolex isn’t a brand that chases hype; it crowns legacy. And now, at just 21, Coco Gauff has joined the same league as Federer, Serena, and Tiger Woods. But the moment the announcement dropped, something strange happened — celebration quickly turned to silence. Some players congratulated her, others… just disappeared from the spotlight. Because when one athlete rises this fast, it doesn’t just inspire people — it shakes them. So what really happened behind the scenes of this historic deal? Is Coco’s success rubbing people the wrong way… or is it simply jealousy disguised as silence?
